2. Strange trees\par
Days passed since my birthday and last journal entry. I am trying to avoid socializing as much as possible, that whole party tired me down not going to lie. That does not mean I don't want to use my limited time left before school starts again to go out in the nature. What I do usually these days is walk by the pond, as well in the nearby forests. No plan, just walking and more walking. My parents keep me warning against wandering alone in the forest, but you know what? I want to take risks. I sometimes hope I lose myself in the vast forest, waking up in a different world. \par
I go out with intention to explore the forest, maybe do some sketching. This was a cold early autumn morning for me, September sometimes feels like it's winter. In my rush to go out I forget to take with me thicker clothes. No time to turn back now, I move fast, sneaking past some people felling logs, reaching an opening in the forest where I am all alone. Quiet, isolated and relaxing I'd say. \par
The falling leaves, red, yellow, brown, all seemed to compliment my presence. Birds chirping happily, going abvout their business. With such views, I grab out of my backpack some crayons and a notepad. I started drawing all kind of sketches, a bit too many, rough and unfinshed. I am unsure what I actually want to accomplish. Nature is beautiful, but my talent not so much, ha. In frustration, I crumpled the drawings and walked towards some stones, one step at a time, as the ground was slippery from all of the fallen tree leaves. As I was about to sit on one of the two stones overseeing this side of the hill, I heard a loud crack. My leg just cracked something. Blowing the leaves away, an old skull could be seen, pierced by my boot, however largely intact. Outside the missing lower end, I could see it's a wolf skull most probably. Thinking of what to do, it struck me! I started sketching the skull, placing it neatly on the stone. This cadre was perfect, and not long after I had a sattisfactory result. \par
The cold has started to seep into my body, creeping in like an annoying reminder that I forgot to wear thicker clothes. Putting everything back in the backpack, preparing to leave, I could not avoid thinking of what happened last time. About that dream. And about the boy. Why I felt so differently when it all happened? It felt almost magical, surreal. I return back to the place and pick up the crumpled sketches and look at them once again, trying to feel something towards them, but no pride or desire to continue it. I felt ridiculed by non-existing people, feeling like my art is worthless, meaningless, just for fun.\par
Before I could continue my train of thoughts, a sound demanded my attention. From a bush with some leaves still on, I could hear something slowly making it's way, rattling the leaves. My eyes were fixated on the bush. To my surprise, it was just a friendly squirrel, happily collecting provisions for the upcoming winter. Nearby it, I spotted a hedgehog. The squirrel quickly climbed a tree, while I was staring at the hedgehog, drawing a raw sketch of it's silhouette. The harsh cold was getting me, I could feel my head aching. I had to go back home sadly. I quickly took off some rocks of the ground, for my private collection. To be honest with you all, I do not know why, I am not a rock nerd, but I do love shiny rocks, so in the bag they go! \par
Going alongside the bushes, on the same trail back home, I could not ignore the fact that there were different trees in the previous spot that I just passed by. Despite the bushes being the same as before, the trees were gone, replaced by ones with darker wood, and looking a bit unnatural. It did not make sense, but as I wanted anyway a cup of hot chocolate and to write more in my diary, I sprung past the trees \f1\lang1048 and was on my way back. However, I had a small panic attack when I could not find my way home. It seemed as if I either forgot the path or the layout shifted somehow. It lasted only five minutes, minutes where I was worried, curious and focused. I felt vulnerable, and that felt strangely pleasant, albeit I would like to avoid such happenings again. After a bit of thinking and pure chance, I was able to figure out the trail back home. \f0\lang1033 The weather was making me lose sanity, probably.\lang9\par
My mother seemed busy in the bathroom and my dad was busy reading in the living room. I profited and quickly made my way upstairs, and in my safety of my home, I could write a bit more. Before playing games again, I remembered of him, albeit struggling, especially to preserve live those minutes in the bed, I just feel an impulse to do so. I am also feeling dread from reminding myself of the dreams, of that boy-monster, whatever that was, still haunting me kinda.\f1\lang1048  My mother berated me quickly, barging in my room and asking me to work more\f0\lang1033 , reasoning I don't help her enough with daily chores\f1\lang1048 . She looked over one of my sketches still lying on the table, \f0\lang1033 scoffing at it, telling me it's a waste of time and I should focus on this new school year\f1\lang1048 . \par
\f0\lang1033 Taking it back from her, being the sketch with the skull on the stone, I was visibly upset, but I could not muster enough will to stand up for my own. I felt once more stressed, pressed all the time to perform, to be "better", to be as she wants me to. It kills my mood and desire to do anything, reduces me to a zombie. I tried to sleep earlier, bored and stressed. \par
This time, I dreamt of a long red carpet, on which I was, leading to a crooked forest, with a black sky and no eyes to be seen. I could still feel their gaze though. In the distance, I saw a boy, however, I did not dare to get closer like last time, so I just sat on the carpet, waking up eventually. \lang9\par
By next day, I was packing my things for school, preparing myself. I decided that this year I will take the journal with me, as well that I will try to date a girl, a bold step for me! I had my eyes on her for a while now. She is quiet, like me, and seems to read, at least from my little amount of stalking I did during classes. I could feel nervous and somehow happy, maybe not for that place, but maybe for the new opportunities. Who knows, maybe we will have new colleagues or I will get to her heart. My mind spiraled down, sinking itself in mindless thoughts, as I finally prepared everything for tomorrow. This time, I got myself notebooks for drawing exclusively, because last years, all of my crappy notes were fighting for space with my cool pen drawings. Should have seen my mom's face trying to figure out what each was. She was not okay with it, but regardless, that will not stop me doodling in class. One of my teachers even gave me a rubik cube to concentrate better.\par
I used to ace all of my school subjects, but because I never had to put real effort into learning, I started lagging behind when things got more difficult. Nowadays, I pray I can pass at some of these subjects. History is one of them. Talking of school, a fun thing that occured a while ago is that the history teacher, she was proud that nobody can cheat in her classroom. My colleague behind me begged to differ, cheating while she was in front of the class. All that boasting and no skills. He was using his phone, tucked away between his two legs, looking at the paper, then at the phone, then at the paper, you get the idea.\par
While I never liked cheating much, I did help colleagues cheat during tess, the good samaritan and all that. ;)\par
Enough of that, my mother is calling me downstairs for dinner. We sat at the dinner table, in silence. The atmosphere felt heavy, just as maybe something happened. Slowly, I made my way to the table, sitting on my chair. I started to reach for the food, when my mom slapped my hand and clasped her hands.\par
- First, the prayers. Let's pray together, like we used to. My mother looked around the dinner table, stopping my dad from gulping his first bite.\par
Trying to pray, I could not shake off the feeling, they were hiding something. What are they up to, why they're reminiscing about the past again? Lately we've been missing some of the prayers, and even eating separately at times. My parents were very fixated on praying before each meal... Their eyes seem to betray them.\par
Nevertheless, I quickly finish my prayers, as always. My stomach is calling me. They made my favourite dish, Hungarian goulash. We used to travel a bit around the world, I saw Budapest with them like four years ago, among other locations. Their food rocks, I wish we were Hungarian so we could always cook such bangers like this goulash soup. Hot, a bit spicy and well seasoned. It has cooked potatoes and bell peppers in the mixture. When I enjoy something, I eat it all in several minutes. Why though my parents sometimes seem to be actually supportive of me, but often they fall on deaf ears or worse, they punish me for the most minor things? I wish they were different. \par
I begin preparing for the next day with great care, but as I looked over the sketches I made, \f1\lang1048 I could not shake the feeling that something was odd. I was able to see two sketches of the weird trees in the forest. I do not remember doing it, do I? I did spend a lot trying my artistic talent, but I do not remember sitting down to draw those trees. So they were real?\f0\lang1033  I did not want to waste any more time on anything else, so I put myself to sleep. \lang9\par
\par
